sentence.text: In the present study, we silenced negative regulation of transcription, DNA-templated expression in pancreatic cancer cell lines and identified the positive roles of CBX3 in cancer cell proliferation.

Furthermore, we demonstrated that silencing negative regulation of transcription, DNA-templated in pancreatic cancer cells inhibited aerobic glycolysis, the basis for providing cancer cells with building blocks for macromolecule synthesis and ATP that required.

To search for the underlying molecular mechanism, we turned to examine the negative regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II of negative regulation of transcription, DNA-templated on the expression of fructose 6-phosphate metabolic process, a negative regulator of aerobic glycolysis in pancreatic cancer and indicated that CBX3 negatively regulated FBP1 expression.

entity.text: negative regulation of transcription by RNA polymerase II

sentence.text: Silencing fructose 6-phosphate metabolic process expression attenuated the decrease in glycolytic capacity that caused by negative regulation of transcription, DNA-templated knockdown in pancreatic cancer cells.

Taken together, these data reveal that negative regulation of transcription, DNA-templated serves as a positive regulator of aerobic glycolysis via suppressing of the fructose 6-phosphate metabolic process in pancreatic cancer cells.
Disrupting the negative regulation of transcription, DNA-templated-fructose 6-phosphate metabolic process signaling axis would be effective to treat pancreatic cancer and prevent aerobic glycolysis
